    "content": "<p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:var(--ds-color__static-content-secondary);font-family:TradeGothic, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:30px;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;color:var(--ds-color__static-content-secondary);font-family:TradeGothic, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:18px;line-height:30px;\">When it comes to Python web frameworks, Django and Flask are two of the most popular.</strong></p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:var(--ds-color__static-content-secondary);font-family:TradeGothic, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:30px;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"color:var(--ds-color__static-content-secondary);font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:400;line-height:30px;\">We’ve already created a whole </span></span><a style=\"background-color:transparent;border-bottom-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1px;box-sizing:border-box;color:var(--ds-color__int-content);font-size:18px;line-height:30px;text-decoration:none;transition:all 0.4s ease 0s;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://careerfoundry.com/en/blog/web-development/django-framework-guide/\"><span style=\"color:var(--ds-color__int-content);font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:400;line-height:30px;\"><strong>beginner’s guide to the Django framework</strong></span></span></a><span style=\"color:var(--ds-color__static-content-secondary);font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:400;line-height:30px;\">, so now let’s take a look at its tiny (but mighty) sibling.</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:var(--ds-color__static-content-secondary);font-family:TradeGothic, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:30px;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"color:var(--ds-color__static-content-secondary);font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:400;line-height:30px;\">So, what is Flask? Flask is a microframework for developers, designed to enable them to create and scale web apps quickly and simply. Explaining how they go about doing that will take a little more unraveling.</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:var(--ds-color__static-content-secondary);font-family:TradeGothic, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:30px;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"color:var(--ds-color__static-content-secondary);font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:400;line-height:30px;\">First, we’ll briefly go over the main ways in which web developers use Python in digital systems, then we’ll introduce the Flask microframework itself.</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:var(--ds-color__static-content-secondary);font-family:TradeGothic, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:30px;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"color:var(--ds-color__static-content-secondary);font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:400;line-height:30px;\">Next, we’ll take a look at some of the pros and cons of using it, and compare Flask with its more well-known stablemate, Django.</span></span></p>",
